01:23:26.293 --> 01:23:27.585
He's not.

01:23:27.628 --> 01:23:29.420
All right?

01:23:29.505 --> 01:23:31.214
Nuke, do you know who this is?

01:23:32.007 --> 01:23:33.758
This is Sandy Grimes.

01:23:33.801 --> 01:23:37.387
Sandy Grimes hit .371
in Louisville in 1967.

01:23:37.429 --> 01:23:39.597
.376.

01:23:39.640 --> 01:23:44.060
I'm sorry. He hit .376.
That's a career, man.

01:23:46.772 --> 01:23:48.981
- In any league.
- Got that right.

01:23:49.066 --> 01:23:52.860
Did you hear what I said?
I'm going to the Show.

01:23:53.696 --> 01:23:57.198
You know what the difference
between hitting .250 and .300 is?

01:23:58.450 --> 01:24:00.243
It's 25 hits.

01:24:01.078 --> 01:24:05.289
Twenty-five hits
in 500 at-bats is 50 points. Okay?

01:24:05.332 --> 01:24:08.084
There's six months in a season.
That's about 25 weeks.

01:24:08.127 --> 01:24:11.462
That means if you get
just one extra flare a week. Just one.

01:24:11.505 --> 01:24:13.965
A gork. You get a ground ball.

01:24:14.007 --> 01:24:16.300
You get a ground ball with eyes.

01:24:16.343 --> 01:24:18.636
You get a dying quail.

01:24:20.222 --> 01:24:24.684
Just one more dying quail a week
and you're in Yankee Stadium.

01:24:25.811 --> 01:24:28.980
You still don't know
what I'm talking about, do you?

01:24:29.022 --> 01:24:30.982
Get the hell out of here.

01:24:31.233 --> 01:24:32.775
All right.

01:24:33.235 --> 01:24:34.861
Fuck.

01:24:35.529 --> 01:24:37.071
Send you a postcard.

01:24:37.156 --> 01:24:39.157
Send me a postcard? Hey, I made it.

01:24:39.199 --> 01:24:40.658
You made it. You made shit.

01:24:40.701 --> 01:24:42.702
Hey! Hey!

01:24:45.831 --> 01:24:46.998
You crazy?

01:24:47.040 --> 01:24:48.916
What the hell's wrong with you?

01:24:49.001 --> 01:24:51.961
- I'll be all right.
- I'm talking about my mirror.

01:24:53.422 --> 01:24:55.423
Shit, I'm sorry. Hey!

01:24:55.507 --> 01:24:57.675
I'm not gonna fight you, man.
I'm not gonna fight you.

01:24:57.760 --> 01:24:59.761
What do you mean,
you're not gonna fight me, you fuck?

01:24:59.845 --> 01:25:02.054
- Fuck. Why am I a fuck?
- Why are you a fuck?

01:25:02.139 --> 01:25:03.723
Because you got talent.

01:25:03.974 --> 01:25:06.726
I got brains, but you got talent.

01:25:07.895 --> 01:25:11.314
See this right arm?
Worth a million bucks a year.

01:25:11.356 --> 01:25:14.108
All my limbs put together
aren't worth seven cents a pound.

01:25:14.193 --> 01:25:16.027
What are you talking about?
You're a great catcher.

01:25:16.069 --> 01:25:19.030
- I'm a great catcher?
- Yeah.

01:25:19.406 --> 01:25:20.656
- Forget it.
- Hey.

01:25:20.699 --> 01:25:22.700
- Fucking forget it.
- Hey, Meat.

01:25:25.913 --> 01:25:27.121
Damn!

01:25:28.832 --> 01:25:30.917
I didn't mean to hit you, man.

01:25:33.253 --> 01:25:35.463
You hurt my eye!

01:25:37.508 --> 01:25:39.133
Sorry.

01:25:39.218 --> 01:25:42.887
Did you hit me with your right hand,
did you hit me with your left?

01:25:44.640 --> 01:25:47.642
Did you hit me with your right hand,
did you hit me with your left?

01:25:47.726 --> 01:25:50.269
- My left.
- Good. That's good.

01:25:50.354 --> 01:25:54.690
When you get in a fight with a drunk,
you don't hit him with your pitching hand.

01:25:55.067 --> 01:25:58.194
God, I can't keep giving you
these free lessons.

01:25:58.237 --> 01:26:00.738
So quit screwing around and help me up.

01:26:07.412 --> 01:26:09.205
You look great, man.

01:26:20.300 --> 01:26:22.218
Be careful with the bags.

01:26:22.845 --> 01:26:25.221
We got a boy going to the Show.

01:26:54.418 --> 01:26:56.335
Sorry about last night.

01:27:00.340 --> 01:27:01.716
Forget it.

01:27:05.178 --> 01:27:09.974
I have been known on occasion
to howl at the moon.

01:27:11.768 --> 01:27:13.311
You understand?

01:27:18.317 --> 01:27:19.817
No.

01:27:20.485 --> 01:27:22.028
Well, you will.

01:27:24.364 --> 01:27:25.781
Look, Nuke,

01:27:26.241 --> 01:27:29.327
these big-league hitters are going
to light you up like a pinball machine

01:27:29.369 --> 01:27:31.996
for a while, all right?

01:27:32.039 --> 01:27:33.956
Don't worry about it.

01:27:33.999 --> 01:27:37.668
You be cocky and arrogant,
even when you're getting beat.

01:27:39.504 --> 01:27:41.005
That's the secret.

01:27:43.175 --> 01:27:47.219
You gotta play this game
with fear and arrogance.

01:27:49.181 --> 01:27:50.765
Fear and ignorance.

01:27:52.184 --> 01:27:56.729
No, fear and arrogance,
you hayseed, not ignorance.

01:27:56.813 --> 01:27:58.356
I know. I know.

01:27:59.524 --> 01:28:02.026
I just like seeing you get all worked up.

01:28:08.325 --> 01:28:09.533
Listen.

01:28:13.372 --> 01:28:14.580
Thanks.

01:28:32.015 --> 01:28:33.224
Hey, Nuke.

01:28:36.019 --> 01:28:37.395
Good luck.

01:28:37.729 --> 01:28:40.731
You too, Meat.

01:29:01.044 --> 01:29:03.212
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

01:29:03.255 --> 01:29:05.256
You may kiss the bride.

01:29:37.998 --> 01:29:42.334
Jimmy, we all pitched in,
and we got you a little gift.

01:29:42.419 --> 01:29:43.502
Tony.

01:29:43.587 --> 01:29:46.756
Kind of a special wedding cake
from the Durham Bulls.

01:29:50.385 --> 01:29:52.303
Oh, my Lord!

01:29:56.975 --> 01:29:58.768
Yeah, Skip?

01:29:59.978 --> 01:30:01.896
You wanted to see me?

01:30:02.647 --> 01:30:06.108
Crash, shut the door.

01:30:11.073 --> 01:30:12.531
I wanna thank everyone!

01:30:12.616 --> 01:30:14.366
Give me a piece of that!

01:30:26.546 --> 01:30:29.507
This is the toughest job a manager has.

01:30:32.844 --> 01:30:34.136
But...

01:30:37.140 --> 01:30:39.642
The organization wants to make a change.

01:30:40.852 --> 01:30:45.731
Now that Nuke's gone,
they wanna bring up some young catcher.

01:30:45.816 --> 01:30:48.192
Some kid hitting .300 in Bluefield.

01:30:48.235 --> 01:30:50.152
He's probably a bust.

01:30:50.946 --> 01:30:54.115
I put in a word for you
with the organization.

01:30:54.199 --> 01:30:58.577
Told them I thought you might make
a fine minor-league manager someday.

01:31:01.123 --> 01:31:05.626
There might be an opening
at Visalia next year.

01:31:08.713 --> 01:31:10.756
You had a hell of a year, Crash.

01:31:12.342 --> 01:31:13.551
But...

01:31:14.719 --> 01:31:16.554
you know how it is.

01:32:39.930 --> 01:32:41.847
I got released.

01:32:42.933 --> 01:32:44.475
I heard already.

01:34:01.052 --> 01:34:03.053
Oh, my.

01:35:01.196 --> 01:35:03.655
I think probably with my love
for four-legged creatures

01:35:03.740 --> 01:35:06.617
and hooves and everything,
that in another lifetime

01:35:06.659 --> 01:35:09.453
I was probably Catherine the Great
or Francis of Assisi.

01:35:09.496 --> 01:35:11.455
I'm not sure which one.

01:35:12.749 --> 01:35:14.458
What do you think, honey?

01:35:16.586 --> 01:35:21.006
How come in former lifetimes
everybody is somebody famous?

01:35:26.471 --> 01:35:27.971
I mean...

01:35:30.392 --> 01:35:33.477
How come nobody ever says
they were "Joe Schmoe"?

01:35:33.561 --> 01:35:36.855
Because it doesn't work that way,
you fool.

01:35:45.532 --> 01:35:47.449
God, you are gorgeous.

01:35:50.161 --> 01:35:51.870
You wanna dance?

01:36:07.178 --> 01:36:08.262
Yes.

01:36:09.013 --> 01:36:10.431
I guess you do.

01:38:45.211 --> 01:38:47.462
Crash took off at dawn.

01:38:47.505 --> 01:38:50.007
Said he heard there might be
an opening for a catcher in Asheville

01:38:50.091 --> 01:38:52.092
in the South Atlantic League.

01:38:53.052 --> 01:38:55.012
A woman should be
so strong and powerful

01:38:55.054 --> 01:38:57.639
that she's not affected by such things.

01:38:57.974 --> 01:39:00.183
I mean, it wasn't the first time
I went to bed with a guy

01:39:00.268 --> 01:39:02.311
and woke up with a note.

01:39:02.687 --> 01:39:05.355
At least the son of a bitch
left me breakfast.

01:39:08.067 --> 01:39:12.195
You have to respect a ballplayer
who's just trying to finish the season.

01:39:12.363 --> 01:39:14.615
At least, that's what I told myself.

01:39:15.575 --> 01:39:18.827
Baseball may be a religion
full of magic, cosmic truth

01:39:18.870 --> 01:39:21.997
and the fundamental ontological
riddles of our time,

01:39:22.206 --> 01:39:24.207
but it's also a job.

01:39:25.960 --> 01:39:29.212
Come on, Meat.
Throw me that weak-ass shit.

01:39:30.048 --> 01:39:32.591
Come on.
You ain't getting that cheese by me.

01:39:32.800 --> 01:39:36.720
Bring it. Bring it. Bring it.

01:39:37.764 --> 01:39:42.726
When Crash hit his 247th home run,
I knew the moment it happened.

01:39:42.810 --> 01:39:44.728
But I'm sure nobody else did.

01:39:45.146 --> 01:39:48.565
And The Sporting News
didn't say anything about it.

01:39:49.942 --> 01:39:53.111
"Full many a flower is born
to blush unseen,

01:39:53.196 --> 01:39:57.324
"And waste its sweetness
on the desert air." Thomas Gray.

01:39:58.076 --> 01:40:01.411
Or William Cullen Bryant.
I don't know. I get 'em mixed up.

01:40:01.746 --> 01:40:05.707
Anyway, my attempts at housekeeping
were feeble as usual.

01:40:05.750 --> 01:40:08.502
I sometimes get easily distracted.

01:40:08.878 --> 01:40:12.172
Funny thing was
I stopped worrying about Nuke.

01:40:12.256 --> 01:40:14.800
Somehow I knew nothing would stop him.

01:40:14.884 --> 01:40:18.970
The world is made for people
who aren't cursed with self-awareness.

01:40:19.180 --> 01:40:22.182
Crash was right, Nuke had a gift.

01:40:22.266 --> 01:40:26.228
I'm just happy to be here,
and I hope I can help the ball club.

01:40:26.437 --> 01:40:28.313
You know, I just wanna
give it my best shot.

01:40:28.398 --> 01:40:30.524
And the good Lord willing,
things will work out.

01:40:30.608 --> 01:40:32.818
You know, you gotta play 'em
one day at a time, though.

01:40:32.902 --> 01:40:35.028
Raye Anne, right? That's a beautiful name.

01:40:35.113 --> 01:40:38.365
Is that Greek? Raye Anne.
It's a beautiful name.

01:40:38.449 --> 01:40:40.951
There's a great song by Motley Crue.
Do you know it?

01:40:41.035 --> 01:40:43.370
"Raye Anne, she's a stay in." No?

01:40:43.454 --> 01:40:45.539
Anyway, a good friend of mine
used to say,

01:40:45.623 --> 01:40:47.499
"This is a very simple game."

01:40:47.583 --> 01:40:50.127
"You throw the ball,
you catch the ball, you hit the ball."

01:40:50.169 --> 01:40:53.380
"Sometimes you win, sometimes you lose."

01:40:53.631 --> 01:40:56.174
"Sometimes it rains."

01:40:56.592 --> 01:40:58.468
Think about that for a while.

01:41:45.224 --> 01:41:47.434
Oh, my.

01:42:31.020 --> 01:42:32.521
What happened?

01:42:34.232 --> 01:42:35.398
I quit.

01:42:38.069 --> 01:42:40.529
Hit my dinger and I hung them up.

01:42:47.119 --> 01:42:49.079
I'm quitting too.

01:42:49.121 --> 01:42:51.331
I mean, boys, not baseball.

01:42:54.043 --> 01:42:58.255
There might be an opening for a manager
in Visalia next spring.

01:43:02.677 --> 01:43:05.387
Think I could make it
to the Show as a manager?

01:43:07.473 --> 01:43:09.432
You'd be great.

01:43:11.435 --> 01:43:13.019
You'd be great.

01:43:14.814 --> 01:43:19.109
I mean, because you understand
about nonlinear thinking.

01:43:19.151 --> 01:43:23.655
I mean, baseball seems like a linear game
with all those lines and box scores.

01:43:23.739 --> 01:43:26.283
But the fact is, it's a spacious
non-time kind of time to it.

01:43:26.325 --> 01:43:27.450
Annie.

01:43:28.578 --> 01:43:29.744
What?

01:43:30.329 --> 01:43:33.164
I got a lot of time to hear your theories.

01:43:33.708 --> 01:43:36.459
And I wanna hear every damn one of them,

01:43:38.546 --> 01:43:42.048
but now I'm tired and I don't want
to think about baseball.

01:43:42.133 --> 01:43:44.426
And I don't wanna think
about quantum physics.

01:43:44.468 --> 01:43:46.887
And I don't wanna think about nothing.

01:43:51.225 --> 01:43:52.851
I just wanna be.

01:43:55.271 --> 01:43:57.188
I can do that, too.

01:43:59.609 --> 01:44:04.154
Walt Whitman once said,
"I see great things in baseball."

01:44:04.238 --> 01:44:07.282
"It's our game. The American game."

01:44:07.325 --> 01:44:10.660
"It will repair our losses
and be a blessing to us."

01:44:11.329 --> 01:44:12.829
You could look it up.

